## Phase 3: Callback — Pending Install Branch [DONE]

### Overview

Add a branch to `processOAuthCallback` that handles the "no orgId" case: fetch GitHub org info, check the 1:1 constraint, insert into `pendingInstallations`, redirect back to the app.

### Changes Required:

#### 3.1 Add `resolveGitHubOrgInfo` helper

**File**: `api/platform/src/lib/oauth/callback.ts` (new function before `processOAuthCallback`)

```ts
interface GitHubOrgInfo {
  accountId: string;
  accountLogin: string;
  accountAvatarUrl?: string;
}

async function resolveGitHubOrgInfo(
  providerName: SourceType,
  externalId: string,
  providerDef: ReturnType<typeof getProvider>,
  config: unknown
): Promise<GitHubOrgInfo | null> {
  if (providerName !== "github") return null;

  const auth = providerDef.auth;
  if (auth.kind !== "app-token" || !("getAppToken" in auth)) return null;

  const jwt = await auth.getAppToken(config as never);
  const response = await fetch(
    `https://api.github.com/app/installations/${externalId}`,
    {
      headers: {
        Authorization: `Bearer ${jwt}`,
        Accept: "application/vnd.github+json",
        "X-GitHub-Api-Version": "2022-11-28",
      },
      signal: AbortSignal.timeout(10_000),
    }
  );

  if (!response.ok) {
    throw new Error(`GitHub API error: ${response.status} ${response.statusText}`);
  }

  const data = githubAppInstallationSchema.parse(await response.json());
  if (!data.account) {
    throw new Error("GitHub installation has no account");
  }

  return {
    accountId: String(data.account.id),
    accountLogin: data.account.login,
    accountAvatarUrl: data.account.avatar_url,
  };
}
```

Import `githubAppInstallationSchema` from wherever it's exported in Phase 1.6.

#### 3.2 Add pending install branch to `processOAuthCallback`

**File**: `api/platform/src/lib/oauth/callback.ts`
**Changes**: After `processCallback` returns and before the existing reactivation detection (line 274), insert a new branch when `orgId` is absent.

Add new imports at top:

```ts
import { pendingInstallations } from "@db/app/schema";
import { providerAccountInfoSchema } from "@repo/app-providers";
```

After `result.status === "pending-setup"` check (line 271), add:

```ts
// ── Pending install: no orgId → store in pendingInstallations, redirect ──
if (!orgId) {
  const githubOrgInfo = await resolveGitHubOrgInfo(
    providerName,
    result.externalId,
    providerDef,
    config
  );

  if (!githubOrgInfo) {
    throw new Error("Could not resolve GitHub organization info");
  }

  // 1:1 constraint check: reject if this GitHub org is already connected
  const existingBinding = await db
    .select({ id: gatewayInstallations.id })
    .from(gatewayInstallations)
    .where(
      and(
        eq(gatewayInstallations.provider, providerName),
        eq(gatewayInstallations.providerOrgId, githubOrgInfo.accountId)
      )
    )
    .limit(1);

  if (existingBinding.length > 0) {
    throw new Error("This GitHub organization is already connected to a workspace");
  }

  const accountInfo = providerAccountInfoSchema.parse(result.accountInfo);

  // Upsert pending installation (idempotent on provider + externalId)
  await db
    .insert(pendingInstallations)
    .values({
      provider: providerName,
      externalId: result.externalId,
      providerOrgId: githubOrgInfo.accountId,
      providerOrgLogin: githubOrgInfo.accountLogin,
      providerOrgAvatarUrl: githubOrgInfo.accountAvatarUrl,
      connectedBy,
      providerAccountInfo: accountInfo,
    })
    .onConflictDoUpdate({
      target: [
        pendingInstallations.provider,
        pendingInstallations.externalId,
      ],
      set: {
        providerOrgId: githubOrgInfo.accountId,
        providerOrgLogin: githubOrgInfo.accountLogin,
        providerOrgAvatarUrl: githubOrgInfo.accountAvatarUrl,
        connectedBy,
        providerAccountInfo: accountInfo,
      },
    });

  await storeOAuthResult(state, {
    status: "completed",
    provider: providerName,
  });

  log.info("[oauth/callback] pending install stored", {
    provider: providerName,
    providerOrgId: githubOrgInfo.accountId,
    providerOrgLogin: githubOrgInfo.accountLogin,
  });

  return buildRedirectForCompletion(stateData, providerName, {});
}
```

The `buildRedirectForCompletion` will use `stateData.redirectTo` (set to `/account/teams/new` in Phase 2.6), redirecting the user back to the teams page where they'll see their pending install.

